1.title: Season's Change

episode of.title: Dark Rising: Warrior of Worlds (TV Series 2014– )

1.plot: Nathan Mallstrom, during a routine shift deep in Clean El Mines, finds The Tether, an ancient artifact believed to be the original link between this Earth and Dark Earth. When The Tether transfers its power to him he finds himself teleported to the Demon World and back again, bringing some unwanted visitors with him. Summer Vale and Bluo arrive to save the day but are left with more questions than answers. They try to explain to Nathan exactly how his new powers will affect his life and the responsibility they brings.

2.title: The Trankartak

episode of.title: Dark Rising: Warrior of Worlds (TV Series 2014– )

2.plot: On the run from Nacelle and Rosemary, Nathan heads into town to seek his sisters help. Ending up cornered by Rosemary, Nathan is aided by Davidath who is injured in the confrontation. While Summer battles Rosemary, Davidath is brought to Gwen's Clinic to try to save his life, where he reveals he has something for Summer; The Trankartak. An ancient black sword that steals the life force of it's victims and grants it to it's wielder, Summer soon has to put her new weapon to the test.

3.title: Connections

episode of.title: Dark Rising: Warrior of Worlds (TV Series 2014– )

3.plot: Summer returns to Paris to meet with her contact while Nathan and Bulo handle things in Nickel City. After placing a protective shield around Gwen's Clinic, Nathan finds out he may need some help with his new powers. Bulo offers a trip to see an old friend who might be able to help, Weeber. When removing The Tether doesn't work, Weeber thinks of a way for Nathan to control it instead and not a second too late as the team has to go on a hunt without Summer.

4.title: Revelations

episode of.title: Dark Rising: Warrior of Worlds (TV Series 2014– )

4.plot: Sckraab, ruler of Dark Earth, arrives to put into place the final pieces he needs to enact his plan. He desires to bring his armies over using The Teather to conquer and rule both worlds. His true evil Is revealed as he shows exactly how far he is willing to go to make this a reality. Summer discovers her true origin and comes to terms with the role she must play in stopping Sckraab and his minions.

5.title: In Sckraab We Trust

episode of.title: Dark Rising: Warrior of Worlds (TV Series 2014– )

5.plot: The team is still dealing with the hard hit Sckraab just dealt them, but they pull together to devise a plan to bring all of this to an end. Summe rhas a final showdown with Rosemary, and Nathan visits Nacelle and Sckraab at the mine for the battle of a lifetime. When Nathan is captured, Aramas reveals the "real plan" to Summer. She must now make a choice to decide the fate of two worlds and nothing will ever be the same again.

imdb.plot outline: There are two Earths. Our Earth is a place where magic and Demons are things of folklore and legend. Dark Earth, is a dimension created in the high middle ages to separate us from Demons and other creatures, ushering in a new age. Man was left in peace, safe for the most part from the demon onslaught. A mythical object known as the Tether remains hidden on this Earth. This object is the key to keeping both Earths apart and allows for a large passageway between both worlds when activated. The Tether had been lost for centuries. During a routine shift at Clean El Mines, Nathan Mallstrom, a local miner, finds himself in the middle of an ancient battle between the Earths when he stumbles onto the Tether during one of his shifts and the object transfers its power to him. Summer Vale joins and guides him as a war for the fate of both worlds rages on with Nathan directly in the eye of the storm.
